## 13. Consolidated Environment Management

### Current State

Every project has its own `.env` and `.env.example`:

| Project | Env File |
|---------|----------|
| B-A-P | `.env` (3199 bytes) |
| Integration | `.env` (2969 bytes) |
| Money | Loads from `config.py` |
| ISN | `.env` (539 bytes) |
| Citadel | `.env` secured in Phase 2 |

### Solution: Workspace Environment Manager

The existing `scripts/bootstrap_env.sh` should be extended:

```bash
#!/usr/bin/env bash
# scripts/bootstrap_env.sh — Enhanced ReliantAI Environment Manager
set -euo pipefail

SECRET=$(python3 -c "import secrets; print(secrets.token_urlsafe(64))")

PROJECTS=("B-A-P" "Money" "integration" "intelligent-storage" "Citadel" "citadel_ultimate_a_plus")

for proj in "${PROJECTS[@]}"; do
    EXAMPLE="$proj/.env.example"
    TARGET="$proj/.env"

    if [[ ! -f "$EXAMPLE" ]]; then
        echo "⚠️  No .env.example for $proj, skipping"
        continue
    fi

    if [[ -f "$TARGET" ]]; then
        echo "✅ $proj/.env already exists, skipping (use --force to overwrite)"
        continue
    fi

    cp "$EXAMPLE" "$TARGET"

    # Inject generated secrets
    sed -i "s|AUTH_SECRET_KEY=.*|AUTH_SECRET_KEY=$SECRET|g" "$TARGET"
    sed -i "s|SESSION_SECRET=.*|SESSION_SECRET=$SECRET|g" "$TARGET"
    sed -i "s|DISPATCH_API_KEY=change-me-in-env|DISPATCH_API_KEY=$(python3 -c "import secrets; print(secrets.token_urlsafe(32))")|g" "$TARGET"

    echo "✅ Created $TARGET"
done

echo ""
echo "🔑 Generated shared secret (AUTH_SECRET_KEY): ${SECRET:0:16}..."
echo "💡 All services will use the same JWT secret for cross-service verification."
```

